Anastasia died of natural causes at a local hospital in 5-01-2020. On 05-04-2020 the hospital notified the Will County Coroner that no relatives could be found. We took custody of the body and the case at that time.

notes.description:
From our investigation we determined that Anastasia was born in Greece, was ethnic Macedonian. While a child was abducted and brought to Romania where she was abandoned. The Roman Catholic church raised her from age 14. She became a high school teacher, got married to Dimitru Enake and later relocated to Yougoslavia. In 1981she came to America on Visa applied for asylum which was later granted.  She claimed a husband Dimitru Enake and son (possible name Pavel Trainan) were in Bucharest Yougoslavia. She married Mihai Gregory Streza  in Will County Illinois 1985. There is no evidence of children in the USA.  We found no solid evidence of any children during our investigation. Her husband Streza is dead.  She was buried by her church.
She listed her parents as Vasilis Cociu and Cristina Cociu.
 Extra DNA cards filed for possible familial research.
